<script>WH.ads.addBodyAd('scrollto_ad_1')</script><h2 class="section-heading hidden" onclick="javascript:mfTempOpenSection(1)">
<div class="mw-ui-icon mw-ui-icon-element indicator"></div>
<span class="mw-headline" id="Steps">Steps</span>
</h2>
<div class="mf-section-1 collapsible-block" id="mf-section-1">
<div class="section steps  steps_first sticky">
<h3 class="in-block">
<div class="altblock"><div>Method <span>1</span><span class="method_of_count"> of 3:</span>
</div>
</div>
<span class="mw-headline" id="Adjusting-Your-Mindset">Adjusting Your Mindset</span>
</h3>
<div id="steps_1" class="section_text">
<ol class="steps_list_2">
<li id="step-id-00">
<a name="step_1_1" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="step_num">1</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Get support from other parents and homeschool teachers.</b> If you've been out of school for a while and suddenly find yourself with the role of "teacher," you probably feel pretty overwhelmed. Thankfully, there are a lot of resources you can take advantage of. Post on forums or join social media groups dedicated to homeschooling during the pandemic. The people there can be a wealth of knowledge and support!
<ul><li>You might also talk to parents who regularly homeschool their kids to get a better idea of what their schedule and learning objectives look like.</li></ul>
<script>WH.performance.mark('step1_rendered');</script>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
<div class="wh_ad_inner" data-service="adsense" data-slot="4313551892" data-width="728" data-height="90" data-type="toc" data-medium="1" data-large="1" data-channels="2156319155,5941219836,7475474614" data-mobilechannels="5941219836,7928712280,9252820051,6429618073,1213291005" data-observerloading="1" data-gptdisplaylate="1"><div id="toc_ad_1"></div></div>
<script>WH.ads.addBodyAd('toc_ad_1')</script><div class="wh_ad_inner" data-channels="5941219836,7475474614" data-mobilechannels="5941219836,7928712280,9252820051,6429618073,1213291005" data-observerloading="1" data-gptdisplaylate="1"><div id="step_ad_1"></div></div>
<script>WH.ads.addBodyAd('step_ad_1')</script>
</li>
<li id="step-id-01">
<a name="step_1_2" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-8.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 8" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/9/9d/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="e6e95041109296eaa31221ca20012975" onload="WH.performance.clearMarks('image1_rendered'); WH.performance.mark('image1_rendered');" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9d/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('e6e95041109296eaa31221ca20012975')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 8" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9d/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/9/9d/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="e6e95041109296eaa31221ca20012975" onload="WH.performance.clearMarks('image1_rendered'); WH.performance.mark('image1_rendered');"></noscript>
<script>WH.performance.clearMarks('image1_rendered'); WH.performance.mark('image1_rendered');</script><div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/9\/9d\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/9\/9d\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-8.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">2</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Remind yourself why youre homeschooling in the first place.</b> Instead of viewing your situation as homeschooling, view it as a necessary part of keeping your children safe during the COVID-19 pandemic. It's okay if you struggle a bitwhat's most important is keeping your family healthy.
<ul><li>Homeschooling can be tough, especially if youre adjusting to a crisis like COVID-19. On the more stressful days, remind yourself that youre helping your children stay educated and well-adjusted during an uncertain time.</li></ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-02">
<a name="step_1_3" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-9.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 9" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/c/cd/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="93f20316571ac68f93e61ab88a170dd8" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cd/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('93f20316571ac68f93e61ab88a170dd8')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 9" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cd/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/c/cd/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="93f20316571ac68f93e61ab88a170dd8"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/cd\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/c\/cd\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-9.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">3</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Practice gratitude on a daily basis with your household.</b> Take a few minutes with your kids to write out or sketch something that each of you is thankful for. Additionally, plan out 1 thing you want to accomplish during the day, along with 1 thing you can stop worrying about.<sup id="_ref-1" class="reference trusted" aria-label="Link to Reference 1"><a href="#_note-1">[1]</a><span class="ts_popup trustedsource" hidden id="ts_popup_1" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<a class="ts_trustworthy" href="/wikiHow:Delivering-a-Trustworthy-Experience">Trustworthy Source</a>

		<span class="ts_name">Greater Good Magazine</span>
		<span class="ts_description">Journal published by UC Berkeley's Greater Good Science Center, which uses scientific research to promote happier living</span>

				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank">Go to source</a>
</span></sup>
<ul><li>For instance, you can say something like: Im thankful for the opportunity to spend more time with my family. Today, Im going to help my kids with a science experiment. Im going to forget about any stress and meltdowns from yesterday and make today the best it can possibly be.</li></ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-03">
<a name="step_1_4" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-10.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 10" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/6/6f/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="953588fa19a382b26281ecadf361db13" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6f/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('953588fa19a382b26281ecadf361db13')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 10" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6f/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/6/6f/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="953588fa19a382b26281ecadf361db13"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6f\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/6\/6f\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-10.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">4</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Adjust your expectations on a day-to-day basis.</b> Try not to expect the world of yourself or your children. Homeschooling is tricky, and itll only seem more stressful and overwhelming if you set your expectations sky-high. Accept the fact that your children may not be as productive as you'd like them to be, which is okay.<sup id="_ref-2" class="reference" aria-label="Link to Reference 2"><a href="#_note-2">[2]</a><span class="ts_popup " hidden id="ts_popup_2" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<span class="ts_name">Research source</span>
		<span class="ts_description"></span>
				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank"></a>

</span></sup>
<ul><li>For instance, dont expect your kids to sit and study for 8 hours each day. Instead, focus on giving them an engaging, thorough education that meshes within your own work schedule.</li></ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-04">
<a name="step_1_5" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-11.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 11" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/7/75/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="9603096ac7c25aac6f90c8001755b39e" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/75/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('9603096ac7c25aac6f90c8001755b39e')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 11" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/75/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/7/75/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="9603096ac7c25aac6f90c8001755b39e"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/75\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/7\/75\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-11.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">5</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Switch up your teaching style if your kids arent as interested.</b> Pay attention to how your kids react and engage with each lesson. Certain teaching styles may not resonate well with your childrenif this is the case, dont be afraid to change it up. Make your lessons more hands-on, or include more visual guides. Keep a close eye on your kids and see what types of lessons resonate with them the most.<sup id="_ref-3" class="reference" aria-label="Link to Reference 3"><a href="#_note-3">[3]</a><span class="ts_popup " hidden id="ts_popup_3" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<span class="ts_name">Research source</span>
		<span class="ts_description"></span>
				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank"></a>

</span></sup>
<ul>
<li>For instance, if your kids arent a fan of reading out loud, have them listen to audiobooks instead.</li>
<li>If your children arent engaged with a lecture, add in some posters and visual aids.</li>
<li>If your kids seem bored and cooped up, move to the front porch or backyard for a change of scenery.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
<div class="wh_ad_inner" data-service="dfp" data-adunitpath="/10095428/engl/engl_gam_lgm_meth1" data-size="[728, 90]" data-apsload="1" data-aps-timeout="2000" data-width="728" data-height="90" data-large="1" data-channels="5941219836,7475474614" data-mobilechannels="5941219836,7928712280,9252820051,6429618073,1213291005" data-observerloading="1" data-sizes-array="[728, 90]" data-gptdisplaylate="1"><div id="method_ad_1"></div></div>
