<script>WH.ads.addBodyAd('mobilemethod_ad_1')</script>
</li>
</ol>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="section steps  sticky">
<h3 class="in-block">
<div class="altblock"><div>Method <span>2</span><span class="method_of_count"> of 3:</span>
</div>
</div>
<span class="mw-headline" id="Reducing-Stress-with-a-Routine">Reducing Stress with a Routine</span>
</h3>
<div id="steps_2" class="section_text">
<ol class="steps_list_2">
<li id="step-id-15">
<a name="step_2_1" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-1.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 1" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/a/a6/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="25cf280f85d319dcea285a18d2ad3cf4" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a6/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('25cf280f85d319dcea285a18d2ad3cf4')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 1" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a6/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/a/a6/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="25cf280f85d319dcea285a18d2ad3cf4"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/a6\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/a\/a6\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">1</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Outline a <a href="/Make-a-Homeschool-Schedule" title="Make a Homeschool Schedule"><b class="whb">rough schedule</b></a> for each day.</b> Develop some realistic goals for your family as well as your individual kids, which will help you know what to focus on for the day. With the entire household in mind, plan out a schedule that you can realistically manage and balance with other obligations you have, like your job.<sup id="_ref-4" class="reference" aria-label="Link to Reference 4"><a href="#_note-4">[4]</a><span class="ts_popup " hidden id="ts_popup_4" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<span class="ts_name">Research source</span>
		<span class="ts_description"></span>
				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank"></a>

</span></sup>
<ul><li>For instance, you might start the day with breakfast and clean up, then let your kids work on assignments while you focus on your job. At this point, you can have lunch, followed by a bit more studying or quiet time. Finish off the day with a fun or social activity, like going for a walk or kicking a ball around outside, to keep your kids engaged.</li></ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-16">
<a name="step_2_2" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-2.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 2" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/6/6d/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="7f6a0d5bce68afed0c08f8ea40377237" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6d/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('7f6a0d5bce68afed0c08f8ea40377237')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 2" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6d/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/6/6d/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="7f6a0d5bce68afed0c08f8ea40377237"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6d\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/6\/6d\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">2</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Divide your day into large blocks instead of specific classes.</b> Regimented classes and segments can seem both overbearing and overwhelming, and may add a lot of unnecessary stress to your schedule. Instead, try to leave your childrens homeschooling schedule more open-ended. Dont schedule subjects within a certain blockinstead, give yourself an open-ended period of time where you can work through multiple subjects.<sup id="_ref-5" class="reference" aria-label="Link to Reference 5"><a href="#_note-5">[5]</a><span class="ts_popup " hidden id="ts_popup_5" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<span class="ts_name">Research source</span>
		<span class="ts_description"></span>
				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank"></a>

</span></sup>
<ul>
<li>For example, you can schedule 1 block of time between 8:30 AM and 1:00 PM. Instead of planning rigid timetables, plan to go through math, reading, and writing during that time. In the afternoon, you can have a second block between 2:00 PM and 5:00 PM, where you focus on science and history.</li>
<li>Blocks offer a lot more flexibility to your schedule, which can help reduce your stress levels.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-17">
<a name="step_2_3" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-3.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 3" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/c/ca/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="4a4ee5214f4a7b1f759826fd4a1b3f18" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ca/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('4a4ee5214f4a7b1f759826fd4a1b3f18')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 3" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ca/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/c/ca/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="4a4ee5214f4a7b1f759826fd4a1b3f18"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/ca\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/c\/ca\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">3</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Give yourself more time than you actually need for lessons.</b> Anticipate that you might run into roadblocks throughout the day, like an extra-challenging lesson or a temper tantrum. Factor extra time into your schedule so your child doesnt fall too far behind in their studies in the event of a big distraction. Dont beat yourself up if you cant keep to a perfect scheduleits perfectly normal to run into issues or unexpected surprises each day.<sup id="_ref-6" class="reference" aria-label="Link to Reference 6"><a href="#_note-6">[6]</a><span class="ts_popup " hidden id="ts_popup_6" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<span class="ts_name">Research source</span>
		<span class="ts_description"></span>
				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank"></a>

</span></sup>
<ul><li>For instance, if itll take 3.5 hours to teach your children math, reading, and writing, set aside 4.5 hours for the block.</li></ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-18">
<a name="step_2_4" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-4.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 4" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/2/29/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="8458e3df3572e146b04b4418fc8ec16d" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/29/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('8458e3df3572e146b04b4418fc8ec16d')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 4" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/29/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/2/29/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="8458e3df3572e146b04b4418fc8ec16d"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/2\/29\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/2\/29\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">4</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Multi-task if youre caring for more than one kid.</b> Prioritize your younger kids first, as theyll need more supervision and focus. Encourage your older kids to work on their studies independently while you sort things out with your little ones. Try to sprinkle naps and breaks into your schedule to help keep your kids refreshed and ready to learn.<sup id="_ref-7" class="reference" aria-label="Link to Reference 7"><a href="#_note-7">[7]</a><span class="ts_popup " hidden id="ts_popup_7" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<span class="ts_name">Research source</span>
		<span class="ts_description"></span>
				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank"></a>

</span></sup>
<ul>
<li>For instance, if you have 3 young children, you can encourage 2 of them to play together while you focus on one child.</li>
<li>Teens can typically work more independently than younger kids, so they might be able to complete an assignment alone while you help another child.</li>
<li>If you have a baby at home, turn your nursing time into storytime for other young children.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-19">
<a name="step_2_5" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-5.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 5" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/8/8e/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="96c894e4947ce4d583d6c4e98a1b5ba2" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8e/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('96c894e4947ce4d583d6c4e98a1b5ba2')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 5" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8e/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/8/8e/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="96c894e4947ce4d583d6c4e98a1b5ba2"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/8e\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/8\/8e\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">5</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Be flexible with your daily routine.</b> Dont be hard on yourself if things dont always go according to plan. Prepare for the unexpected, especially if youre juggling a full-time job and other responsibilities along with your homeschooling duties. Switch up the learning schedule and give your kids extra time to finish assignments if theyre having trouble finishing up in 1 day. Going with the flow is a normal part of homeschooling, and nothing to be ashamed of.<sup id="_ref-8" class="reference trusted" aria-label="Link to Reference 8"><a href="#_note-8">[8]</a><span class="ts_popup trustedsource" hidden id="ts_popup_8" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<a class="ts_trustworthy" href="/wikiHow:Delivering-a-Trustworthy-Experience">Trustworthy Source</a>

		<span class="ts_name">Greater Good Magazine</span>
		<span class="ts_description">Journal published by UC Berkeley's Greater Good Science Center, which uses scientific research to promote happier living</span>

				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank">Go to source</a>
</span></sup>
<ul><li>Being flexible doesnt take away from the quality of your kids schooling.</li></ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-110">
<a name="step_2_6" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-7.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 7" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/a/a4/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="a59963d01089f140c274f5436f9cb88b" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a4/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('a59963d01089f140c274f5436f9cb88b')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 7" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a4/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/a/a4/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="a59963d01089f140c274f5436f9cb88b"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/a4\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/a\/a4\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">6</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Set aside some time for yourself.</b> Once the school and work day is over, give yourself a small chunk of time to catch your breath, relax, and do anything that helps take the edge off. Try going for a walk, drawing a warm bath, reading a book, or doing anything else that helps you chill out and organize your thoughts.<sup id="_ref-9" class="reference" aria-label="Link to Reference 9"><a href="#_note-9">[9]</a><span class="ts_popup " hidden id="ts_popup_9" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<span class="ts_name">Research source</span>
		<span class="ts_description"></span>
				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank"></a>

</span></sup>
<ul><li>If you don't have a partner, carve out some time for yourself after your kids go to bed.</li></ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-111">
<a name="step_2_7" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-6.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 6" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/6/66/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="409b59853db98cdbca6ddd2e26518400" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/66/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('409b59853db98cdbca6ddd2e26518400')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 6" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/66/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/6/66/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="409b59853db98cdbca6ddd2e26518400"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/66\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/6\/66\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">7</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Spend some quality time with your partner, if you have one.</b> Arrange some time at the end of the day where you can relax with your partner and compare notes about anothers days. Offer support and a listening ear to your partners worries, and share any of your own stressors or worries that you have about homeschooling. These types of conversations can really help you relieve stress on a daily basis.<sup id="_ref-10" class="reference" aria-label="Link to Reference 10"><a href="#_note-10">[10]</a><span class="ts_popup " hidden id="ts_popup_10" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<span class="ts_name">Research source</span>
		<span class="ts_description"></span>
				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank"></a>

</span></sup>
<ul><li>For instance, you can say something like: Im worried that the kids arent really engaged in the curriculum. Can you think of ways I can make things more interesting?</li></ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
<div class="wh_ad_inner" data-service="adsense" data-slot="7710650179" data-width="728" data-height="90" data-smallheight="250" data-type="method" data-small="1" data-medium="1" data-channels="5941219836,7475474614" data-mobilechannels="5941219836,7928712280,9252820051,6429618073,1213291005" data-observerloading="1" data-gptdisplaylate="1">
