</li>
</ol>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="section steps  sticky">
<h3 class="in-block">
<div class="altblock"><div>Method <span>3</span><span class="method_of_count"> of 3:</span>
</div>
</div>
<span class="mw-headline" id="Planning-for-Rough-Days">Planning for Rough Days</span>
</h3>
<div id="steps_3" class="section_text">
<ol class="steps_list_2">
<li id="step-id-212">
<a name="step_3_1" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-12.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 12" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/5/54/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="bc6c97949590a7e2d672414f8b13850a" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/54/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('bc6c97949590a7e2d672414f8b13850a')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 12" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/54/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/5/54/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="bc6c97949590a7e2d672414f8b13850a"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/5\/54\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/5\/54\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-12.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">1</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Identify the root of your childs problems as they arise.</b> Dont view a meltdown or temper tantrum at face value. Instead, think about any stressors that are contributing to your childs behavior. Try to separate yourself from the problem and understand that your childs issues are independent and separate from you.<sup id="_ref-11" class="reference trusted" aria-label="Link to Reference 11"><a href="#_note-11">[11]</a><span class="ts_popup trustedsource" hidden id="ts_popup_11" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<a class="ts_trustworthy" href="/wikiHow:Delivering-a-Trustworthy-Experience">Trustworthy Source</a>

		<span class="ts_name">Greater Good Magazine</span>
		<span class="ts_description">Journal published by UC Berkeley's Greater Good Science Center, which uses scientific research to promote happier living</span>

				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank">Go to source</a>
</span></sup>
<ul>
<li>For instance, if a child throws a temper tantrum, their emotions may stem from feelings of stress or being overwhelmed.</li>
<li>If your teen seems particularly moody, they may be missing their friends or extracurricular activities.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-213">
<a name="step_3_2" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-13.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 13" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/d/d9/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="ad92884284696c58bdf0922bfd599b0b" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d9/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('ad92884284696c58bdf0922bfd599b0b')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 13" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d9/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/d/d9/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="ad92884284696c58bdf0922bfd599b0b"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d9\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/d\/d9\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-13.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">2</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Write a list of calming activities for yourself and your children.</b> Sit down with your kids and brainstorm some activities that help you all relax and unwind. These dont have to be complicated or fancyinstead, view these activities as life preservers that can rescue you from a tough situation. Place the finished list in an area where everyone can see it, like the refrigerator.<sup id="_ref-12" class="reference trusted" aria-label="Link to Reference 12"><a href="#_note-12">[12]</a><span class="ts_popup trustedsource" hidden id="ts_popup_12" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<a class="ts_trustworthy" href="/wikiHow:Delivering-a-Trustworthy-Experience">Trustworthy Source</a>

		<span class="ts_name">Greater Good Magazine</span>
		<span class="ts_description">Journal published by UC Berkeley's Greater Good Science Center, which uses scientific research to promote happier living</span>

				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank">Go to source</a>
</span></sup>
<ul>
<li>For instance, some calming activities might be going for a walk, listening to relaxing music, or playing with a favorite toy.</li>
<li>If your child has a meltdown, you can help them relax by giving them a few minutes to do a calming activity.</li>
<li>Teens might enjoy texting with their friends or playing a video game.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-214">
<a name="step_3_3" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-14.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 14" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/6/64/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="df08d280b608e2a90588a82918c1edee" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/64/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('df08d280b608e2a90588a82918c1edee')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 14" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/64/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/6/64/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="df08d280b608e2a90588a82918c1edee"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/64\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/6\/64\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-14.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">3</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Calm your child down before disciplining them.</b> Dont lash out at your child while theyre having a tantrum. Instead, help them calm down in a healthy way, like time out. Express empathy to your child, explaining that you understand how theyre feeling.<sup id="_ref-13" class="reference trusted" aria-label="Link to Reference 13"><a href="#_note-13">[13]</a><span class="ts_popup trustedsource" hidden id="ts_popup_13" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<a class="ts_trustworthy" href="/wikiHow:Delivering-a-Trustworthy-Experience">Trustworthy Source</a>

		<span class="ts_name">Greater Good Magazine</span>
		<span class="ts_description">Journal published by UC Berkeley's Greater Good Science Center, which uses scientific research to promote happier living</span>

				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank">Go to source</a>
</span></sup>
<ul><li>Dont say things like: You cant behave like this! Instead, you can say something like: I understand that youre feeling upset, but yelling isnt going to fix anything. Lets take some deep breaths instead.</li></ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li id="step-id-215">
<a name="step_3_4" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-15.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 15" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/f/ff/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="572c51833e0eece99b97aacc49a7b1b9" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/ff/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('572c51833e0eece99b97aacc49a7b1b9')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 15" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/ff/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/f/ff/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="572c51833e0eece99b97aacc49a7b1b9"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/ff\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/f\/ff\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-15.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">4</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Practice mindfulness as you go through the week.</b> Pretend like youre a third-person observer in your mind. Instead of addressing every negative or stressful thought in your head, simply watch these thoughts and let them float away. Focus on staying grounded in the current moment instead of worrying about the past or future.<sup id="_ref-14" class="reference" aria-label="Link to Reference 14"><a href="#_note-14">[14]</a><span class="ts_popup " hidden id="ts_popup_14" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<span class="ts_name">Research source</span>
		<span class="ts_description"></span>
				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank"></a>

</span></sup>
<ul><li>For instance, if you get a thought that involves worrying about your upcoming schedule for the week, let it pass instead of focusing on it.</li></ul>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
</li>
<li class="final_li" id="step-id-216">
<a name="step_3_5" class="stepanchor"></a><div class="mwimg  largeimage  floatcenter " style="max-width:728px"><a href="#/Image:Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-(for-Parents)-Step-16.jpg" class="image"><div class="content-spacer">
<img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 16" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/0/08/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="b59aae259f5ae1587d483c3f8abd0e2b" data-src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/08/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg"><script>WH.shared.addScrollLoadItem('b59aae259f5ae1587d483c3f8abd0e2b')</script>
</div>
<noscript><img alt="Image titled Cope with the Stress of Homeschooling (for Parents) Step 16" src="https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/08/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg" decoding="async" class="whcdn content-fill" data-srclarge="/images/thumb/0/08/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg" data-width="460" data-height="345" id="b59aae259f5ae1587d483c3f8abd0e2b"></noscript>
<div class="image_details" style="display:none;"><span style="display:none;">{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/08\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg\/v4-460px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/0\/08\/Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg\/aid12076176-v4-728px-Cope-with-the-Stress-of-Homeschooling-%28for-Parents%29-Step-16.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"&lt;div class=\"mw-parser-output\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a9 2020 wikiHow, Inc. All rights reserved. wikiHow, Inc. is the copyright holder of this image under U.S. and international copyright laws. This image is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;\/b&gt; licensed under the Creative Commons license applied to text content and some other images posted to the wikiHow website. This image may not be used by other entities without the express written consent of wikiHow, Inc.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br \/&gt;\n&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;\/div&gt;"}</span></div></a></div>
<div class="step_num">5</div><div class="step">
<b class="whb">Ask friends and family for support if you need it.</b> Call or text your loved ones if youre having a bad day. Theyll be able to offer a listening ear and some advice, especially if they have kids of their own. Above all, focus on the fact that youre not alone, and that you have plenty of loved ones who will help you get through the challenges that homeschooling has to offer.<sup id="_ref-15" class="reference" aria-label="Link to Reference 15"><a href="#_note-15">[15]</a><span class="ts_popup " hidden id="ts_popup_15" style="display: none;">
	<span class="ts_close">X</span>
		<span class="ts_name">Research source</span>
		<span class="ts_description"></span>
				<a href="#" class="ts_source" target="_blank"></a>

</span></sup>
</div>
<div class="clearall"></div>
